column35:
the current headless-tests.js have a lot of embedded promise-based calls, like below:

functionA()
.then(
   function(result) {
      // do stuff
      functionB()
      .then(
         function(result) {...});
   });

this is defeating the purpose of the design of Promise-based APIs, it should have been chained like below (note the "return" statement on the call to functionB()):

functionA()
.then(
   function(result) {
      // do stuff
      return functionB();
   })
.then(
   function(result) {...});
);

